Ok, this would be one of those cases where the caption doesn't match the pic but this needs to be mentioned. Long story short, I left my H wallet in a cab this morning, and somehow it ended up in the hands of a Vietnamese student who was headed to the airport. He went out of his way to leave it at the airport's police post before presumably leaving for his flight home. I was contacted, headed to the airport where I collected my wallet with all its contents intact. Thank you Mr Le, because of you my hope in all humanity has been reaffirmed today.
